-- Pacers Beat Hawks 107-90 in Opening Game of NBA Playoff Series
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2013-04-21T19:39:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-21/pacers-beat-hawks-107-90-in-opening-game-of-nba-playoff-series.html
Paul George  scored 23 points and
had 11 rebounds and 12 assists as the Indiana Pacers defeated
the Atlanta Hawks 107-90 in the first game of their National
Basketball Association playoff series.  The teams will return to Bankers Life Fieldhouse in
Indianapolis on April 24 for Game 2 in the best-of-seven first-
round series.  Also today in the Eastern Conference, the NBA champion
Miami Heat host the Milwaukee Bucks in the opening game of their
series. In the Western Conference, the Los Angeles Lakers visit
the  San Antonio Spurs  and the Oklahoma City Thunder host the
Houston Rockets.  On the first day of the postseason yesterday, the New York
Knicks rallied past the Boston Celtics 85-78 and the Brooklyn
Nets routed the Chicago Bulls 106-89 in the Eastern Conference.
In the West, the Denver Nuggets edged the Golden State Warriors
97-95 and the  Los Angeles Clippers  eased to a 112-91 victory
over the Memphis Grizzlies.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  